.TH "device_release_driver" 9 "device_release_driver" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
device_release_driver \- manually detach device from driver.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" device_release_driver
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Manually detach device from driver.
When called for a USB interface, \fIdev->parent\fP lock must be held.

If this function is to be called with \fIdev->parent\fP lock held, ensure that
the device's consumers are unbound in advance or that their locks can be
acquired under the \fIdev->parent\fP lock.
